The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD 

 (Landmark, Rs 799)

 A look at the career of Swedish rock band Europe through video clips, live performances and archive footage. Highlights include the hits Final Countdown and Carrie, and the title track, the quintet?s first Swedish number one. 

 THE SHOW

 (Oxford Bookstore, 6.30 pm, September 12)

 The screening of The Hand of Fate, based on Katherine Mansfield?s The Fly, will be followed by Blues, a stage adaptation of the short story, and a discussion on the two works.

 THE EXHIBITION

 (Gorky Sadan, 5.45 pm September 13)

 The five-day exhibition commemorates the 75th anniversary of Tagore?s visit to Russia. Rabindra Chitralekha features his art works, In Russia At Last has rare photographs of the bard in Moscow, and Tagore in Russia focuses on his literary works.




